etymologies: Middle English: as an other until the 16th century

definitions: used to refer to an additional person or thing of the same type as one already mentioned or known about; one more; a further

examples.text: 170 miles done, only another 100 to go

shortDefinitions: used to refer to additional person or thing of same type as one

definitions: used with a proper name to indicate someone or something's similarity to the person or event specified

examples.text: this will not be another Vietnam
they said she was another Jennifer Aniston

shortDefinitions: used to indicate person or thing's similarity to person or event specified

definitions: used to refer to a different person or thing from one already mentioned or known about

examples.text: his wife left him for another man

shortDefinitions: used to refer to different person or thing

definitions: used to refer to someone or something sharing an attribute in common with the person or thing already mentioned

examples.text: I went to the window and saw one cat being chased by another cat

shortDefinitions: used to refer to someone sharing attribute

definitions: an additional person or thing of the same type as one already mentioned or known about

examples.text: the British poet Philip Larkin is another of his favorite writers
they have two sessions, one in the morning and another in the afternoon

shortDefinitions: additional person or thing of same type

definitions: a different person or thing from one already mentioned or known about

examples.text: they kept moving from one place to another
he may be fit for one type of work but not another
it is one thing to formulate policies and quite another to implement them

shortDefinitions: different person or thing from one already mentioned
